./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:2343:sdp/runner.log:1745:{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-25T19:38:28.399Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1777145908399_0","parameters":{"content":"# Verification Report — T-002@20260425T183959Zd\n\n**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\n**Date:** 2026-04-25\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\n- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis/sampler_effects.scd`\n- `tests/test_sampler_effects.py`\n- `my-claw/supercollider/test_sampler_effects.scd`\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation of the comb-resonance SynthDef in `sampler_effects.scd` matches the requirements:\n- Tuned to B fundamental (61.74 Hz) via `comb_b_freq` default.\n- `comb_decay` (T60) and `comb_damping` (LPF cutoff) controls are correctly implemented and clipped for stability.\n- The FX chain order is correct: Input → Delay → Reverb → Freeze → Comb.\n- The signal flow uses `SelectX.ar` for clean branching and `LocalIn`/`LocalOut` for the feedback delay.\n\n## Completeness\nAll required components are present:\n- `sw_sampler_fx` SynthDef includes all four FX stages.\n- Damping and decay controls are wired into the DSP graph.\n- Python integration tests (`tests/test_sampler_effects.py`) provide exhaustive declarative verification of the SCD source (UGens, arguments, defaults, clipping, and order).\n- SC-side runtime tests (`my-claw/supercollider/test_sampler_effects.scd`) verify non-silent output, freeze-toggle behavior, and the 61.74 Hz spectral peak.\n\n## Consistency\nThe code follows established project conventions:\n- SynthDef naming and bus assignments (stereo at 16) match the Sampler PRD.\n- DSP logic uses standard SuperCollider patterns (`CombC`, `LPF`, `SelectX`).\n- Python tests utilize the established regex-based source validation pattern.\n\n## Security\nNo security vulnerabilities or secret leaks were identified. The changes are strictly DSP and testing logic.\n\n## Quality\nThe code quality is high:\n- Extensive range clipping in the SynthDef ensures numerical stability (e.g., `cbDecay` clipped to 0.05..10.0s).\n- The `cbDampCutoff` formula provides a musically useful transition from \"bright\" to \"woody\" resonance.\n- SC-side tests include automated RMS and FFT-based magnitude checks for objective verification.\n\n## Issues Found\n- None.\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nThe implementation is solid and well-verified. The candidate hardening checks regarding `bootstrap_identity` were also verified to be pre-existing and correctly wired in both `daemon.py` and `cypherclaw_daemon.py`.\n","file_path":"sdp/verification/t-002@20260425t183959zd-verify.md"}}
