./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:2472:- Closed the server-side gap on the new master-bus sampler controls: added a `master_smooth.scd` SuperCollider source stub for `sw_master_smooth` that declares `sampler_amp` and `sampler_bypass_comp` (both default 1.0) alongside the existing `amp` / `drive` / `warmth` / `reverb` / `room` surface; refactored `start_audio.sh` and `restart_composer.sh` to seed the master node via `senseweave.master_bus.master_bus_s_new_args()` so the boot-time `/s_new sw_master_smooth` arg list stays in lockstep with `DEFAULT_MASTER_BUS_VALUES`; added `tests/test_master_smooth_scd.py` to pin the stub's control declarations and the boot scripts' helper-driven seeding.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:2479:- Added executable production-course curriculum exercises: `ExerciseSpec` now carries a runnable `template` and explicit `expected_features` while preserving the legacy `expected` alias; generated exercise specs include both metadata forms; and the EMSD curriculum now has verifier-backed exercises for intervals/scales, chord voicings, progressions, rhythm/groove, counterpoint, synthesis architecture, mix/master, SenseWeave mapping, Theramini ensemble, genre strategy, and full-arc production.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:2481:- Added SuperCollider recipe references for curriculum: created 22 discoverable recipe files in `my-claw/curriculum/recipes/supercollider/` for topics from MIDI-to-frequency to master-bus, linked them from EMSD-102 and EMSD-130 reference docs, and added static validation tests in `tests/test_supercollider_recipes.py` that check for required labels without coupling to the live audio server.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:2482:- Added dissonance/resolution metadata checks to counterpoint rules using music_theory.py interval consonance data: new `DissonanceAnnotation` and `DissonanceReport` dataclasses carry full `Interval` objects from the music theory library; `analyze_dissonance()` annotates each vertical interval in a voice-pair sequence with consonance classification and stepwise resolution status; `verify_resolution_sequence()` validates that all sharp dissonances resolve properly; `resolution_completeness_score()` returns a 0.0-1.0 ratio; and `weighted_voice_leading_smoothness()` penalizes unresolved dissonances in the smoothness metric.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:2486:- Added installation-aware acoustic ecology policies: new `acoustic_ecology.py` module provides `resolve_acoustic_ecology()` which translates presence, cadence, day phase, room activity, attention state, and dwell time into a frozen `AcousticEcologyPolicy` with hard ceilings for volume, onset density, and spectral brightness, silence window parameters, ordered source preferences, keynote privilege weights, and density/voice caps. Sleep and wind-down modes enforce non-negotiable ceilings that cannot be overridden by any modifier. Performance attention overrides wind-down constraints when the human is actively engaged. Room activity boosts keynote privilege so the room's own soundscape is the acoustic content.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:2499:- Added section-level motif development and local harmonic progressions: `tracker_compiler.py` now labels each section as statement, sequence/fragment, contrast inversion, recall answer, liquidation, or residue, reshapes phrase material accordingly, and applies section-local progressions that are exposed on tracker scenes and steps for bass/progression verification.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:2501:- Fixed recalled motif rhythm metadata so later sections that borrow earlier material inherit the current scene's rhythm/progression profile instead of leaking the source scene's old `rhythm_development`.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:2502:- Added arrangement automation curves to tracker playback: `music_tracker.py` now derives `arrangement_curve` from section rhythm, writes row-point automation for `density`, `master_amp`, and `reverb_send`, shapes note velocity across each lane's active window, and `music_tracker_runtime.py` / `duet_composer.py` now expose and apply interpolated automation to the live master bus during the section. Low density also thins optional color/counter runtime events while preserving melody and bass continuity.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:2503:- Fixed a live capture fallback issue that made the sampler lean on a quiet self bus: `room_listener.py` now skips absent named JACK ports and tries direct `jack_rec` fallback ports such as `system:capture_1`, while `sample_dsp_activity.py` now resolves missing `theramini_in` to `contact_mic` / `room_mic` before `self_bus`.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:2505:- Fixed the live score-tree runtime on CypherClaw: `duet_composer.py` now derives commission context defensively from the world when `TrackerPlan` lacks `day_phase` / `weekly_phase`, `master_bus.py` now exposes an explicit `sw_master_smooth` seed helper, and `restart_composer.sh` now reseeds that master node again after the new composer PID is confirmed alive so the first piece does not run with scene-level `/n_set` traffic targeting a dead node.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:2509:- Hardened the slow observer-vision path: `observer_vision.py` now treats Ollama `503 server busy / maximum pending requests exceeded` as queue saturation instead of a user-facing description, preserves the HTTP body detail in `vision_error`, emits a compact local fallback description with `vision_backend: \"local_fallback\"`, and backs off before retrying the multimodal model call again.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:2517:- Added real EMSD master-bus control: `master_bus.py` now translates live `mix_*` fields plus tracker-scene `master_amp` / `reverb_send` automation into `sw_master_smooth` `/n_set` updates at scene start, so EMSD mix intent now shapes the summed output path instead of only per-note rendering.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:2523:- Made the Scarlett recovery path deterministic: when real JACK needs to be rebuilt, `start_audio.sh` now clears stale JACK state, relaunches `jackdbus`, and configures the ALSA backend for `hw:USB` before starting `scsynth`, so the box can recover onto the Scarlett monitor path instead of drifting into a PipeWire-only fallback.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:2539:- Rebalanced EMSD source authority toward the room in lived-in late phases: capstone `Convergence` and `Crystallization` now prefer `room_mic` outside `away_practice`, DSP scene focus follows that same room bias, and `sample_dsp_activity.py` can retarget a sparse late-phase `self_bus` request onto a fresh room capture while still preserving the original requested source in state for operator visibility.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:2540:- Fixed room-capture triggering so external sample sources no longer depend on `self_listener` RMS. `room_mic`, `contact_mic`, and `theramini_in` now trigger from their own live cues, while only `self_bus` remains gated by self-audio level.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:2554:- Folded the highest live octave down by one octave at playback time: `voice_shaping.py` now marks the extreme top band with a `pitch_multiplier`, and `play_voice()` applies that fold before sending OSC so CypherClaw's brightest instruments stop landing in the most painful register.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:2555:- Tightened title-hook coherence again: `hook_engine.py` now chooses title phrases from image-field-aware pools that also react to cadence, progression profile, hook type, and repertoire source titles, so CypherClaw can move between labels like `Low Light`, `Electric Circuits`, `Moving Lines`, and `Open Thresholds` without collapsing back to generic or repeated adjective-noun pairs.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:2556:- Very high-note playback shaping is now stronger and more explicit: `voice_shaping.py` emits best-effort `highpass_hz` and `saturation_mix` controls in addition to the existing top-octave gain/brightness/release shaping, and `play_voice()` forwards those controls so ear-splitting notes can be filtered and driven slightly when the live SynthDefs support it.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:2564:- Extended repertoire influence into tracker form memory: the live composer can now inherit a prior strong song's preferred progression profile, title/hook recall mode, form variant, and section-density bias before building the next tracker song.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:2565:- Made repertoire memory active instead of archival-only: `repertoire_memory.py` now returns forward-looking influence by family/cadence, `hook_engine.py` can answer or recall prior title/hook material, and the live composer can bias the next song's progression profile before score generation begins.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:2571:- Diversified family and harmonic planning across the day and week: `resolve_tracker_plan()` now rotates through day-phase and weekly-phase family palettes instead of pinning occupied daytime songs to one family, and it emits progression profiles like `open_day`, `lift`, `settling`, and `experiment` so the score generator changes chord motion as well as form.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:2572:- Added family-level motif memory to the live tracker path: `ContinuousLearner` now tags songs with tracker family, progression profile, cadence state, and patch context, `MelodicMemory` can retrieve matching fragments by keyword, and `score_from_mood()` now prefers and answers same-family/profile motifs instead of drawing only from a generic recent fragment pool.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:2574:- Gave the named house patches real musical identities instead of just voice pools: `score_from_mood()` is now patch-aware, so melody contour, bass/comping pattern, progression bank, dynamics, and register spread all change with the active house patch.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:2575:- Replaced the provisional tracker patch set with named house patches (`house_monastery`, `house_chamber`, `house_garden`, `house_procession`, `house_workshop`) and retired `bell` / `metal` from live runtime playback, so CypherClaw now stays inside a more coherent western-compatible ensemble even when the cast contains those older inharmonic voices.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:2577:- Replaced the inharmonic runtime `gong` playback voice with a tuned bowed substitute, so the live foundation voice sits inside western/modal harmonic material instead of fighting it.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:2581:- Widened tracker orchestration so CypherClaw can actually use the broader character-instrument registry: cast planning now keeps a support-role character in low-energy songs, tracker role hints recognize metal/grain/pad/tabla synths, and runtime voice routing preserves those explicit lane instruments instead of collapsing them to legacy fallbacks.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:2582:- Tuned tracker voice routing to be lane-aware again after the orchestration widening pass: ringing `metal`/`bell`/`pad` hints are normalized away from long quiet texture/counter lanes, and tracker runtime restores a pad safety fallback so subdued scenes do not sit on a constant unregulated tone.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:2583:- Added cadence-aware tracker voice softening for `wind_down` and sleep-adjacent scenes, so chirpy `pluck`/`kotekan`/`grain` cast hints are remapped toward bowed, breath, choir, or gong voices before late-night playback.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:2585:- Added explicit runtime voice aliases so unavailable or unsafe voices can degrade cleanly: `grain` now resolves to `breath`, and `tabla_ge` currently resolves to `tabla_tin` until a real `sw_tabla_ge` SynthDef is deployed.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:2588:- Added SenseWeave operator diagnostics to daemon `/status`, including score tree, section function, arrangement curve, ear metrics, sample source, master bus, self-listener, and independent rollout flags for curriculum/exercise, preview render, self-critique, and long-form suites.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:2592:- Made CypherClaw tracker solo cast-aware: the live composer now derives tracker lane voice hints from the active character cast and enforces a quiet foundation lane through subdued `Theme`/`Development`/`Recap` scenes.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:2611:- Added a queue-backed Telegram `/monitor` built-in so live queue progress and active task status come from the authority DB instead of stale routed status text.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:2612:- Unified queue-progress totals across Telegram and `sdp-cli`: counts now use live executable tasks and exclude only split parents.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:2616:- Added the missing `OPT-005` half-hour Telegram heartbeat in the live daemon scheduler, including uptime, I/O wait, memory, load, available-agent count, queue progress, pet XP summary, and Observatory logging.
