./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:3129:CypherClaw's signature palette is a quartet: `sw_bell_warm`, `sw_bowed`, `sw_breath`, `sw_pad`. These are synthesis voices — every sound they make is generated from oscillators, filters, and envelopes. They have no memory of the room, no memory of yesterday, no memory of what just happened. Every piece is born from silence.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:3131:This PRD adds a fifth signature voice — **`sw_sampler`** — that elevates the room itself, the artist's recorded history, and a curated found-sound library into a primary instrument. The sampler is **how CypherClaw metabolizes the room**: it listens continuously to the contact mic and room mic, captures fragments worth remembering, and replays those fragments granularly — stretched, transposed, scrubbed, with a dedicated effects bus — back into the live performance.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:3139:3. **Curated found-sound library.** A handpicked `samples/library/` of field recordings, gathered MIDI keyboard captures from Anthony, Theramini phrases, and reference textures. Tagged by character (warm/metallic/wind/pulse/voice/mechanical), pitch, and length. Treated as palette colors, never as sample-pack tropes.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:3143:1. **Granular by default, never one-shot.** The sampler is a granular voice with grain size 20–200 ms, density, position scrub, and pitch transpose. "Press button hear sample" is not a use case. Every play is a re-rendering through grains.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:3145:3. **Effects-bus parity with the rest of the orchestra.** Sampler output routes through a dedicated effects bus (long delay, convolution reverb, spectral freeze, comb resonance to B fundamental). The effects shape the *character of the voice*, not just gloss on top.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:3147:5. **Restraint earned, not eroded.** The sampler joins the quartet to make a quintet, but it does not relax the 3-voice base / 2-voice deliberate / 4-voice climax discipline. Heavy sampler use replaces, not adds. In *Solitary* mode the sampler may be the *only* voice.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:3153:**In scope:** a granular SuperCollider voice (`sw_sampler`) with a dedicated effects bus; a sample library on disk with tag-based selection; a continuous live-capture daemon for contact/room mics; a self-quotation loop; integration with the existing artist-mode selector and cast planner so the sampler joins the signature quintet; metrics and anti-pattern detection for sampler over- or under-use.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:3157:- Full DAW-style multi-track sampler with chopping, slicing, or loop-point editing UI. The sampler is a granular voice, not a workstation.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:3159:- Replacement of any existing signature voice. The quartet stays; the sampler is added to make a quintet.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:3160:- Real-time pitch-tracking sample triggering from human input. Theramini and keyboard capture are *recorded* into the library and replayed through the granular voice — not used as live MIDI-style triggers.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:3166:**Phase 1 — Foundations (CCS-001..CCS-008).** Sample data model, on-disk library layout, tag taxonomy, mood/mode-aware selector, character-registry entry for `voice_sampler`, signature-voice quintet update. Pure Python + tests. At end of phase, the selector picks plausible samples for any (mode, arc, mood) tuple from a library of stub/placeholder files; no audio plays yet.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:3168:**Phase 2 — SuperCollider granular voice (CCS-009..CCS-014).** `sw_sampler.scd` SynthDef with grain-controlled buffer playback; buffer-management protocol for loading samples on demand; dedicated effects bus (delay + reverb + spectral freeze + comb-to-B); mix-engine integration so the sampler routes through the master bus. End of phase: sending OSC `/s_new sw_sampler bufnum=N grain_size=80ms density=12 pitch=0` plays a granular cloud audible through the speakers.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:3172:**Phase 4 — Composer integration (CCS-022..CCS-028).** Mode-driven sampler density (solitary heavy, working light, etc.); `select_sample()` wired into cast/instrument-patch path so the composer treats the sampler as a first-class voice; self-quotation loop captures composer output when arc-payoff is high; keyboard/Theramini capture during human play; per-mode effects-bus presets; operator diagnostics surface currently-active samples. End of phase: pieces start to noticeably *cite themselves* across sessions, and the room's acoustic history becomes audible material.
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:3174:**Phase 5 — Verification + observability (CCS-029..CCS-033).** Per-piece sampler-event metrics; anti-pattern detection for sampler dominating (over-quote) or never appearing (silent quintet member); a sample-usage journal that records which samples played in which pieces with what transformations; end-to-end smoke test on cypherclaw confirming the daemon is capturing, the selector is choosing, the synth is playing, and the self-listener is observing the right output peaks. End of phase: composer can demonstrate a piece that uses 1 self-quotation + 1 room-capture + 1 library sample, all selector-chosen, all routed through the effects bus, all surfaced in the diagnostics dashboard.
