./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:3221:| CCS-009 | Implement `sw_sampler.scd` granular SynthDef with bufnum, grain-size, density, position-scrub, pitch-transpose, attack/release envelope, and effects-bus send. | MUST | T1 | - SynthDef args: `bufnum`, `amp` (default 0.5), `grain_size_ms` (default 80, range 20–200), `density` (default 12 grains/sec), `position` (0..1 normalized), `position_rate` (scrub speed), `pitch_transpose_semitones` (default 0), `pitch_jitter_semitones` (default 0.1), `attack_sec` (default 0.05), `release_sec` (default 0.2), `gate` (default 1, sustained), `out_bus` (default 0), `fx_send` (default 0.4)<br/>- `doneAction:2` self-frees on envelope end<br/>- compiled `sw_sampler.scsyndef` lives in `synthesis/synthdefs/`<br/>- SC-side test (`my-claw/supercollider/test_sw_sampler.scd`) renders 2-second clip from a known buffer and verifies non-silence + spectral characteristics<br/>- gate=0 triggers release tail correctly |
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:3223:| CCS-011 | Implement `sampler_effects.scd` dedicated effects-bus SynthDef chain: long delay (1/4 to 1/2 measure), convolution reverb (FreeVerb fallback if no IR loaded), spectral freeze (PV_Freeze), comb-resonance tuned to B fundamental (61.74 Hz). | MUST | T1 | - SynthDef `sw_sampler_fx` reads from a stereo bus and writes to master bus<br/>- args: `delay_time` (sec, default 0.5), `delay_feedback` (0..0.85, default 0.55), `verb_mix` (default 0.35), `room_size` (default 0.7), `freeze_amount` (0..1, default 0.0), `comb_b_amount` (0..1, default 0.25), `comb_b_freq` (default 61.74)<br/>- bus number conventionally 16 (stereo, so 16+17)<br/>- compiled `sw_sampler_fx.scsyndef` lives in `synthesis/synthdefs/`<br/>- SC-side test verifies non-silent output for a known impulse input and frequency-domain check that 61.74 Hz comb peak is present when `comb_b_amount > 0` |
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:3225:| CCS-013 | Per-voice gate-controlled lifecycle: composer can `play_sampler(record, duration_sec)` for fire-and-forget OR `start_sampler(record) -> handle; stop_sampler(handle)` for sustained voices. | MUST | T1 | - `sampler_dispatch.play_sampler(record, duration_sec, **params)` schedules a fire-and-forget grain cloud with an internal envelope of `duration_sec`<br/>- `start_sampler` / `stop_sampler` returns/uses a handle for sustained sampler voices that match the bowed/pad lifecycle<br/>- both code paths feed through the same `dispatch_sample` core<br/>- tests verify both lifecycles and that they can run concurrently without buffer-id collision |
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:3226:| CCS-014 | Integrate sampler effects bus into `master_bus.py` mix slot with appropriate gain staging (peak-normalized, not RMS) and post-mix compression bypass to preserve grain transients. | MUST | T1 | - `master_bus.apply_master_bus_scene` recognizes a `sampler_bus` mix slot with default gain -3 dB (peak-normalized so quieter library samples don't disappear)<br/>- post-mix compression for the sampler slot has `compression_ratio = 1.5` (lower than the 4.0 used elsewhere) so grain transients survive<br/>- tests verify gain staging on a known-amplitude input and grain-transient preservation via peak-vs-RMS ratio |
./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Za_1777156511.log:3234:| CCS-022 | Wire `SampleSelector` into `cast_planner.select_cast_ids` so when the cast includes `sw_sampler`, a sample is pre-selected for the piece and attached to the cast metadata. | MUST | T1 | - `select_cast_ids` (or a sibling `assemble_cast`) returns cast entries with optional `sample_record: SampleRecord` field for sampler voices<br/>- selection happens once per piece commission and passes mode + arc_phase + mood + target_character (drawn from `instrument_patches.select_instrument_patch`)<br/>- tests verify sampler voices in cast carry a sample_record and that the record matches selector contracts |
