sdp/verification/t-020@20260416t054258z-verify.md:13:All seven frequency lanes (sub, bass, low-mid, midrange, upper-mid, presence, air) are defined in `FREQUENCY_LANES` with correct Hz boundaries. `PRODUCTION_ROLE_FREQUENCY_LANES` maps all seven required roles (bass, pad, lead, texture, noise, sample, theramini) to their respective lanes. `_PRODUCTION_METADATA` includes `hpf_hz`, `lpf_hz`, `eq_intent`, and `stereo_policy` for every required role. Both dicts are attached to `MixProfile` as `role_frequency_lanes` and `production_metadata` in `build_mix_profile`. `build_mix_profile` now assigns a `production_role` string to each `VoiceMixTarget` and corrects voice lane boundaries so bass/melody/counter/color no longer overlap. The acceptance criteria are fully met.
sdp/verification/t-020@20260416t054258z-verify.md:17:The seven required roles are all covered. The three new tests exercise: (1) complete lane assignment coverage, (2) filter/EQ metadata presence for all seven roles, and (3) masking-free lanes with bass stereo center policy. A minor gap: the `noise` role has no corresponding `VoiceMixTarget` in the default `build_mix_profile` (only bass/melody/counter/color are created), so `production_metadata["noise"]` is defined but never bound to an active voice. This is not a blocking omission for this task — the metadata registry is correct and available for future consumers.
sdp/verification/t-020@20260416t054258z-verify.md:29:77 tests pass (0 failures, 0 errors). All three new acceptance-criteria tests pass. The voice lane boundaries were corrected so that bass (30–150 Hz), melody/lead (1200–3500 Hz), counter/pad (180–900 Hz), and color/texture (3500–8000 Hz) are non-overlapping — a concrete improvement in mix correctness beyond just metadata.
sdp/verification/t-020@20260416t054258z-verify.md:33:- [ ] `noise` and `sample` roles have production metadata but no corresponding `VoiceMixTarget` in the default `build_mix_profile` output — minor: not blocking this task but future consumers expecting a voice bound to these roles will not find one.
sdp/verification/t-020@20260416t054258z-verify.md:39:- The `noise` and `sample` metadata entries should be wired to actual `VoiceMixTarget` instances when those voice types are added to the composition pipeline. The registry is ready; the binding is not.
