sdp/verification/t-015@20260416t054258z-verify.md:21:- **Rootless voicings**: Strips root PC, trims optional tones (5ths and 11ths) when >4 voices. Verified: C13 rootless → {2, 4, 9, 10}.
sdp/verification/t-015@20260416t054258z-verify.md:23:- **Voice-leading**: `_voice_leading_cost` uses note-by-note motion + length penalty + center-shift. `choose_voicing` picks the minimum. Test confirms G7 following Cmaj7 resolves to (62, 65, 67, 71) (voice-leading optimized).
sdp/verification/t-015@20260416t054258z-verify.md:39:- `voice_chord` alias for `choose_voicing` is a reasonable ergonomic alias.
sdp/verification/t-015@20260416t054258z-verify.md:49:- Tests verify pitch class correctness, uniqueness of voicings (`len == len(set(...))`), range bounds for all notes, min/max spacing enforcement, and voice-leading optimality.
sdp/verification/t-015@20260416t054258z-verify.md:62:Both open issues are minor and do not affect any acceptance criterion. The chord/voicing engine is complete and correct. If slash-chord bass-voice routing is needed in a future task, add a test pinning the behavior (bass note currently silently stripped). The empty-voicing error path is defensive code that works correctly — a single test covering a very tight register (e.g., `low=60, high=61`) would complete coverage.
