sdp/verification/t-016@20260425t183959zb-verify.md:47:{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-26T01:20:09.709Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1777166409709_0","parameters":{"content":"# Verification Report — T-016@20260425T183959Zb\n\n**Verify Agent:** gemini-cli\n**Date:** 2026-04-26\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\n- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/cast_planner.py`\n- `tests/test_cast_planner.py`\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation correctly wires `SampleSelector` into `select_cast_ids`. It detects if `sw_sampler` is part of the chosen cast and, if so, uses the provided `sample_selector` to pick a sample and attaches its summary to `cast_metadata`. The summary includes `id`, `path`, `source`, and `duration_sec` as requested.\n\n## Completeness\nThe task is complete. It handles the no-sampler case by leaving metadata untouched and also handles cases where `sample_selector` or `cast_metadata` are not provided. Edge cases like `sample_selector.select` returning `None` are also handled.\n\n## Consistency\nThe code follows the existing patterns in `cast_planner.py`. It uses a `Protocol` for `_SampleSelectorLike` to maintain type safety without a hard dependency on the actual `SampleSelector` class (which is owned by another task).\n\n## Security\nNo security issues were identified. The implementation uses standard library features and internal project structures safely.\n\n## Quality\nThe quality of the code is high. The use of a `Protocol` and clear helper functions like `_voice_synth` and `_summarize_sample` makes the code readable and maintainable. New tests provide good coverage for the added functionality.\n\n## Issues Found\n- [ ] No issues found.\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nThe implementation is solid. The use of `getattr` in `_summarize_sample` provides good flexibility for different sample object shapes.\n","file_path":"sdp/verification/t-016@20260425t183959zb-verify.md"}}
