sdp/verification/t-002-verify.md:11:The implementation correctly follows PRD §7.5.2 and CC-071. Each voice calculates its expression intensity as a weighted sum of vibrato depth, tremolo depth, dynamics, and pitch-bend extent. The `AffectiveStateBusWriter` maintains a rolling window of these samples and flushes the mean intensity per voice to the shared OSC control bus.
sdp/verification/t-002-verify.md:14:The implementation is complete for the scope of T-002. It includes the calculation logic, the rolling window management with pruning, and the OSC emission logic. Sorting voices by mean ascending before flushing correctly implements the max-pooling requirement by ensuring the last value written to the bus (which is a single-value control bus) is the highest mean among active voices.
sdp/verification/t-002-verify.md:17:The code follows the established patterns in the project. The Python constants match the SuperCollider bus indices and channel counts. The use of `deque` for the rolling window is an efficient choice for pruning.
sdp/verification/t-002-verify.md:23:The code is well-structured and includes comprehensive unit tests. The tests cover edge cases such as empty windows, out-of-range inputs, and stale voices falling off the window.
sdp/verification/t-002-verify.md:31:The implementation of the per-voice rolling-window intensity writes is solid. The sorting logic in `flush()` is a clever way to handle max-pooling on the SuperCollider control bus without needing complex server-side logic at this stage.
sdp/verification/frac-0102d-verify.md:39:- The contract test is robust and covers all required fragments specified in the technical approach.
