sdp/verification/t-018@20260416t054258zd-verify.md:234:{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-16T21:12:09.365Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1776373929365_0","parameters":{"content":"# Verification Report — T-018@20260416T054258Zd\n\n**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI (VERIFY)\n**Date:** 2026-04-16\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\n- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/music_tracker.py`\n- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/tracker_compiler.py`\n- `tests/test_counterpoint_pipeline.py`\n- `progress.md`\n- `sdp/implementation-plan.md`\n\n## Correctness\n**PASS.** The implementation correctly wires the `counterpoint_relation` metadata through the entire pipeline. \n- In `tracker_compiler.py`, the `Score` metadata is now correctly populated with `production_counterpoint_relation` (via the `PRODUCTION_COURSE_KEYS` loop) and `counterpoint_rule_id`.\n- In `music_tracker.py`, `build_scene_from_score` correctly extracts `production_counterpoint_relation` from the scene metadata and updates every lane with specific counterpoint metadata (max leap, preferred intervals, etc.) resolved from the registry.\n- The `validate_scene_counterpoint` function correctly implements the three required acceptance criteria using the lane analysis helpers.\n\n## Completeness\n**PASS.** All three acceptance criteria are fully covered by the new test suite in `tests/test_counterpoint_pipeline.py`:\n1. **Independent lane contours**: Verified in `TestIndependentLaneContours`.\n2. **Staggered climaxes**: Verified in `TestStaggeredClimaxes`.\n3. **No lane crowding**: Verified in `TestNoLaneCrowding`.\nThe test suite includes both positive cases (valid scenes) and negative cases (scenes with locked contours, concurrent peaks, or overlapping registers), ensuring robust verification.\n\n## Consistency\n**PASS.** The implementation follows established patterns in the SenseWeave tools.\n- Metadata keys follow the `production_*` and `counterpoint_*` naming conventions used elsewhere.\n- The use of `_counterpoint_metadata_for_lane` helper matches the pattern of other metadata-enrichment functions in `music_tracker.py`.\n- The test suite structure is consistent with other pipeline tests.\n\n## Security\n**PASS.** No security issues, secrets, or unsafe practices identified. The changes are limited to music metadata propagation and analysis.\n\n## Quality\n**PASS.** \n- 27 new tests in `tests/test_counterpoint_pipeline.py` pass.\n- All 2615 tests in the project pass, ensuring no regressions.\n- The code is clean, well-documented, and properly typed.\n\n## Issues Found\n- None.\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nThe wiring is complete and the validation logic is sound. Although `validate_scene_counterpoint` is currently only called in the tests, it is ready for integration into the main `validate_scene` or a self-critique loop as needed. The metadata propagation from score to tracker lanes is fully operational.\n","file_path":"sdp/verification/t-018 @20260416t054258zd-verify.md"}}
