sdp/verification/t-033@20260416t181925z-verify.md:19:Role enum (`StrEnum`) defined with all six required members: OSTINATO, MELODY, PAD, PERC, ACCENT, SILENCE. The `grid_locked` property correctly returns `True` for OSTINATO and PERC, `False` for MELODY/PAD/ACCENT, and `None` for SILENCE — matching the spec exactly. `role_is_eligible` updated to use `resolve_role` which handles both `str` and `Role` inputs, rejecting grid-locked and SILENCE roles. All six rules (articulation, final_rit, microtiming, phrase_arch, call_response, motif_memory) delegate `applies_to` to `role_is_eligible`, satisfying the shared filter policy. The render pass consults `applies_to` before dispatching rules to voices.
