sdp/verification/t-008@20260502t001347zd-verify.md:76:{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-05-02T04:20:17.328Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1777695617328_0","parameters":{"file_path":"sdp/verification/t-008 @20260502t001347zd-verify.md","content":"# Verification Report — T-008 @sdp/logs/Verify_T-008_20260502T001347Zd_1777695549.log\n\n**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\n**Date:** Friday, May 1, 2026\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\n- `pyproject.toml`\n- `src/cypherclaw/narrative_api/__main__.py`\n- `src/cypherclaw/narrative_api/app.py`\n- `src/cypherclaw/narrative_api/settings.py`\n- `src/cypherclaw/narrative_api/log_config.py`\n- `tests/test_narrative_api_main.py`\n- `tests/test_narrative_api_entities.py`\n- `tests/test_narrative_api_settings.py`\n\n## Correctness\nThe uvicorn entry point is correctly implemented as a console script `narrative-api` in `pyproject.toml` and via `python -m cypherclaw.narrative_api`. It properly utilizes `NarrativeSettings` (via `pydantic-settings`) to resolve `bind_host` and `bind_port`. The `main()` function in `__main__.py` correctly calls `bootstrap_identity()` for startup hardening before starting the server.\n\n## Completeness\nAll requirements from the task description and the auto-generated hardening bullets have been met. Specifically:\n- Entry points `narrative-api` and `python -m cypherclaw.narrative_api` are functional.\n- Settings are read from environment variables (prefixed with `NARRATIVE_`) or `.env` files.\n- Smoke tests hitting `/health` via `TestClient` are included and pass.\n- Structured logging (`structlog`) and request-logging middleware are integrated.\n- The \"blocking\" requirement for `GET /world/entities` tests is addressed in `tests/test_narrative_api_entities.py`, covering domain filtering (defaulting to `shared`, `deniable` including `shared`), type filtering, and pagination.\n\n## Consistency\nThe implementation follows the established patterns in the codebase, such as the use of `NarrativeSettings` for configuration and the dependency injection pattern in `create_app` for testability. The logging configuration aligns with the structured logging conventions used in other parts of the project.\n\n## Security\nThe API correctly implements shared-secret authentication via the `X-Narrative-Auth` header, controlled by the `auth_token` setting. `NARRATIVE_AUTH_TOKEN` is used to secure the endpoints. No secrets are hardcoded or leaked in logs.\n\n## Quality\nThe code is well-structured, modular, and extensively tested. 85 tests related to the narrative API passed successfully. The `list_world_entities` implementation in `entities.py` includes a robust heuristic for pagination with local filtering to ensure clients receive the requested number of items even when using stores with varying filtering capabilities.\n\n## Issues Found\n- [ ] No issues found. (A pre-existing `PermissionError` in `tests/test_daemon_fallback.py` was observed but determined to be unrelated to the current task scope).\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nThe implementation is solid. The pagination heuristic in `list_world_entities` (`limit * 5` fetch) successfully balances store-side efficiency with local filtering correctness. The ASGI gap mentioned in previous notes is addressed for the primary entry points (`main()`), ensuring `bootstrap_identity()` is invoked during standard startup.\n"}}
